title: Rising seas threaten to flood launch sites, NASA says, including Wallops - WTKR-TV Norfolk
text:
NASA's rockets are astounding machines, capable of blasting into space at thousands of miles per hour and withstanding temperatures twice the melting point of steel. Rising sea levels caused by melting ice caps threaten to disrupt a handful of NASA launch sites along U.S. coastlines, the space agency warns.
